1434,"cache_read_input_tokens":33011,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1434},"output_tokens":10,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"332bfb8d-9e66-4b23-8708-d7c9ef07615c","uuid":"6131c563-f8fa-4c0b-970d-83c2242f8dc0"},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01AM7TA4rxdLfsigxFH6ZnGf","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\"action\":\"spawn_agents\",\"summary\":\"TICKET-0247 is the sole remaining OPEN ticket in M8 Bug Fix phase. It is in the retry queue (3rd attempt). The previous fix (wave 2) created _close_for_travel() to prevent input-re-enable from colliding with TravelSequenceManager, but a new symptom persists: after CONFIRM TRAVEL the player is locked in place and the biome transition never fires. Assigning gameplay-programmer for targeted investigation of the full travel initiation path.\",\"wave\":[{\"agent\":\"gameplay-programmer\",\"ticket\":\"TICKET-0247\",\"budget_usd\":2.50,\"needs_worktree\":true,\"needs_godot_mcp\":true,\"prompt_supplement\":\"RETRY ATTEMPT 3 (final retry allowed by config). This ticket has been through two prior fix cycles:\\n\\n1. Wave 1 fix (commit 894b37f): Corrected fuel unit/cell conversion and BASE_SHIP_WEIGHT so CONFIRM TRAVEL button enables correctly.\\n2. Wave 2 fix (commit a7b8185): Created `_close_for_travel()` in navigation_console.gd to close the panel WITHOUT re-enabling inputs, preventing TravelSequenceManager's input-disable from being undone. Reordered close-before-initiate so fuel_changed callbacks don't update a closing UI.\\n\\nCurrent symptom: After clicking CONFIRM TRAVEL, the player is visibly locked in place (inputs disabled as expected) but the biome transition never triggers — no fade, no scene change, nothing.\\n\\nDebugging guidance:\\n- The input lock confirms `_close_for_travel()` ran and `NavigationSystem.initiate_travel()` was called (since the input disable happens inside TravelSequenceManager._on_travel_completed, which is connected to the travel_completed signal).\\n- HOWEVER: if the signal fires and `_on_travel_completed` is entered but `_fade_out()` hangs or returns early, the transition stalls while inputs remain disabled. Check all early-return paths in TravelSequenceManager.\\n- Verify that `NavigationSystem.initiate_travel()` actually emits `travel_completed` after fuel is consumed — add logging if needed.\\n- Check whether closing the panel before `initiate_travel()` (the wave 2 reorder) affects any node references or signal connections that TravelSequenceManager relies on.\\n- Confirm the TravelSequenceManager node is present in the scene tree and its `_on_travel_completed` handler is connected at the time travel is initiated.\\n- Look for any `await` that could silently stall (e.g., `await get_tree().create_timer(0).timeout` racing with a freed node).\\n\\nAcceptance criteria (all must be met before marking DONE):\\n- Pressing CONFIRM TRAVEL triggers a visible biome transition (fade out → scene load → fade in).\\n- Player inputs are re-enabled after the transition completes (not before).\\n- The selected biome loads correctly.\\n- All existing unit tests pass.\\n- This ticket has a hold condition requiring Studio Head sign-off — do NOT mark DONE; instead, leave a detailed activity log entry confirming all criteria are met and state 'READY FOR STUDIO HEAD SIGN-OFF'.\"}]}"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1434,"cache_read_input_tokens":33011,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1434},"output_tokens":10,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"332bfb8d-9e66-4b23-8708-d7c9ef07615c","uuid":"34c0aa7b-8463-4291-bdf2-e8824ebbb8a3"},{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,